Moneys releaser funkar visst. Jag brände ut CD2 med Alcohol 120% utan problem. Läs NFO-filen om ni inte förstår hur installationen funkar. Everything downloaded fine.  I'm pretty much a noob at this stuff, but somehow I figured out how to make it work.  For all you English-speaking people, here's how it works.  After everything is downloaded, use WinRar to extract the contents of mo-cdufa.001 in CD1 into whatever folder you want.  Then mount the .cue CD1 file onto a drive to install.  When it asks for CD2, you must extract the mo-cdufa.001 CD2 file into a folder, mount it, and then hit OK.  After installation, use Alcohol 120% to create an image.  This will allow you to play the game.  (Oh yeah, you also need to find a CD key.)  For some reason, it only allows me to play MultiPlayer.  Whenever I try to start Single Player, it wants a CD, and I don;t know how to fix that.  If anyone knows how to help, it would be appreciated.  Thanks and good luck with your download.
